// ch05 §5.12: "the borrowed local cannot be ... reassigned ... while the
// closure is still alive." `f`'s last use is `return f();` at the end,
// so its borrow of `x` is still live when `x = 10;` executes -- a direct
// write to the borrowed original, conflicting with the closure's own
// live reference-typed member (mirrors how
// `borrow_released_after_last_use_permits_direct_write` in
// 04_references_borrow shows the *opposite*, permitted case once the
// borrow's last use has already passed).
int main() {
    int x = 5;
    auto f = [&x]() { return x; };
    x = 10;
    return f();
}
